::Fenox::

Fenox turns to look at D as he bumps his cheek against her. She takes 
a small step to the side to regain her balance from it being upset by 
the bump from the larger bot.

"What would you like to see first?" She asks. "There are training 
rooms, equipment storage, and the bridge, where you can meet Zardus 
probably. Oh, and I could also assign you some quarters."




--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:
> 
> 
> 
> * With his head bowed D entered the Iron Fist right behind Fenox, 
his 
> shoulder brushing against her back as he turned slightly to look 
behind him 
> and then to the side to look at the metal walls.
> This was just lik the ship he knew before, only that it didn't have 
the warm 
> musty smell of humans in it. More of a rusty smell was what this 
one smelled 
> like at one sniff, probably because people in metal lived here 
instead.
> D's ears moved in ever direction, taking in the sounds of computer 
consoles 
> and the constant humm of systems as they worked. This was a noisy 
world!
> He turned his head and looked back towards Fenox, wondering just 
what she 
> was going to show him and if he had ever seen anything similar.
> In this ship, there were bound to be wonders.
> D bumped his cheek against her shoulder for a sign to move on, 
eager to find 
> out more.*
